HEADWORD: Sorbite
<hw>Sor"bite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>sorbus</ets>
service tree.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A sugarlike substance,
isomeric with mannite and dulcite, found with sorbin in the ripe berries
of the sorb, and extracted as a sirup or a white crystalline
substance.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>Sor*bit"ic</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

